{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\n\"Surface the same tools we use\" includes visual authoring. The existing editor already enumerates\ncriteria (`prompt_library.enumerate_library`, packaged + `.rebar/prompts/`), authors criterion\nprompts (`create_prompt(kind=criterion)` via the `/library/create` route), and edits routing in\nworkflow YAML — so authoring is incremental. The one genuinely net-new piece is a **live\nmust-fire/must-not-fire preview**: the editor has NO prompt-execution endpoint today (its `POST`\nset is `/save`, `/prompt/save`, `/validate`, `/library/create`). This is a structurally\nindependent deliverable (its own endpoint + spike).\n\n## What\n\n- Extend the editor to author a project criterion end-to-end: prompt + a **routing-fields form**\n  (exec, applies_at/applies_to, block_threshold, default_posture/blocking_enabled, fail_mode) that\n  writes the `.rebar/` overlay + activation, reusing `create_prompt`/`update_prompt`.\n- New **`POST /criterion/preview`** endpoint (synchronous): `{criterion_id | inline(prompt+routing),\n  fixture}` → `{verdict: \"fire\"|\"no-fire\", finding?: <findings.py shape>, rationale: str}`,\n  reusing the story `#3` per-criterion eval runner behind the `agents` extra + credentials, with a\n  **configurable timeout (default 60s)**.\n- **Spike gate (resolve before committing UI):** define the pass/fail — if a single sync preview\n  does not return within the timeout on the reference model, fall back to an **async job+poll**\n  shape (define the job id + poll endpoint) rather than blocking the editor's `ThreadingHTTPServer`\n  handler. Do not leave the sync-vs-async decision unspecified.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Files: `src/rebar/llm/workflow/editor.py` (routes), `editor_assets/` (form + preview UI),\n  `prompt_library.py` (authoring reuse).\n- Depends on story `#1` (overlay/activation to author into) and story `#3` (the runner the preview\n  reuses).\n- Reuse: `enumerate_library`, `create_prompt`/`update_prompt`, the `/library/create` route.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The editor authors a project criterion: prompt + routing-fields form writing the `.rebar/`\n      overlay + `activate` list (reusing `create_prompt`/`update_prompt`).\n- [ ] `POST /criterion/preview` runs a live must-fire/must-not-fire preview with the defined\n      request/response contract, configurable timeout (default 60s), reusing the eval runner.\n- [ ] The spike gate is resolved: a defined pass/fail threshold and a concrete async job+poll\n      fallback if sync execution is infeasible in the editor's HTTP handler.\n- [ ] Authoring + preview work for both an LLM criterion and a DET invariant.\n\n\n## Preview dispatch, entry point & atomic authoring (remediation, run 1)\n\n### Preview entry point — reuse the LANDED runners (clears the reuse-claim blocker)\nBoth halves now exist on `main`:\n- **LLM criterion** (`exec: 1-TURN`/`AGENT`): the preview runs it as its Pass-1 finder over the\n  fixture text via `eval_solver.run_case(prompt_id, {\"input\": <fixture>}, runner=…, repo_root=…)`\n  (the criterion arm added in story 55b8, which wraps `passes.pass1_chunk`). Fire ⇔ non-empty\n  `findings`.\n- **DET invariant** (`exec: DET`): the preview resolves the criterion's `detector` selector and runs\n  the grounding scan the way `plan_review/det_invariants._run_one` does (story 7f0d) — a match ⇒\n  fire, an abstain ⇒ reported per `fail_mode`. (The preview scans the fixture content, not a ticket\n  `file_impact`, since it is an isolated must-fire/must-not-fire probe.)\n\n### `POST /criterion/preview` dispatch (clears the LLM-vs-DET dispatch blocker)\nThe endpoint reads the criterion's `exec` DIRECTLY from its routing/descriptor (NOT `exec_tier`,\nwhich has no DET arm — per 7f0d): `exec == \"DET\"` → the DET path above; else → the LLM path. Request\n`{criterion_id | inline(prompt+routing), fixture:{input, expect?}}` → response `{verdict:\n\"fire\"|\"no-fire\", finding?: <findings.py finding shape>, rationale}`. A criterion that needs a\ngraph/log (container/ISF) → a clear 4xx (not runnable as an inline preview). Synchronous with a\nconfigurable timeout (default 60s); the spike-gate fallback (async job+poll) applies only if a\nsingle sync preview exceeds the timeout on the reference model.\n\n### Atomic dual-write for routing-fields authoring (clears G6 atomic blocker)\nAuthoring a project criterion touches TWO files: `.rebar/prompts/<id>.md` (the rubric, via\n`create_prompt` — already atomic) and the `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` overlay routing entry.\nCoordination: the criterion is only ACTIVE when it is in BOTH the routing map AND the `activate`\nlist (ef7e semantics). The write order is prompt-first, then a single atomic JSON overlay write\n(temp-file + `os.replace`, mirroring `prompt_authoring._atomic_write`). If the overlay write fails,\nthe orphaned `.rebar/prompts/<id>.md` is harmless (a prompt with no active routing never runs). The\noverlay write itself is atomic (no half-written JSON), and adding the id to `activate` is part of the\nSAME overlay write — so activation is all-or-nothing. No partial-active state is reachable.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (remediation additions)\n\n- [ ] `POST /criterion/preview` dispatches on `exec` read directly (DET → grounding scan; LLM →\n      `eval_solver.run_case` criterion arm) and returns `{verdict, finding?, rationale}` for BOTH an\n      LLM criterion and a DET invariant; container/ISF → a clear 4xx.\n- [ ] Routing-fields authoring writes the prompt then a single ATOMIC overlay write (temp+replace);\n      a failed overlay write leaves no active criterion (activation requires the `activate` entry,\n      written atomically with the routing entry).\n\n\n## DET preview materializes the fixture (remediation, run 2)\n\n`engine_b.scan` scans a repo FILESYSTEM, not an inline string — so the DET-criterion preview cannot\nscan `fixture.input` directly. It materializes the fixture into a DISPOSABLE temp dir (reusing the\n`eval_solver.case_store` pattern: `tempfile.TemporaryDirectory` + git init), writes `fixture.input`\nto a file whose name is `fixture.filename` (a new optional fixture field) — defaulting to a name the\ndetector's `languages`/`file_globs` accept (e.g. `preview.py` for a Python-scoped rule; a generic\n`preview.txt` when unconstrained) — then runs `engine_b.scan(tmpdir, registry=<the criterion's\ndetector slice>)`. Fire ⇔ a `match` record on that file; an `abstain` (tool absent) → reported per\n`fail_mode` (open → no-fire/skip, closed → a \"coverage gap\" no-fire note), never a crash. The temp\ndir is removed on exit. (The LLM preview needs no materialization — `pass1_chunk` takes inline\ntext.) So the endpoint's DET arm = materialize→scan; its LLM arm = `run_case` over inline text.\n\n- [ ] The DET preview materializes `fixture.input` into a temp file (named via `fixture.filename` or\n      inferred from the detector's language/globs), scans it with the criterion's detector slice, and\n      maps match→fire / abstain→per-`fail_mode`; a test asserts a planted violation fires and a clean\n      fixture does not.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782888407476676001,"uuid":"f1e16992-0f68-4cc5-90fa-7a7f357062ee"}